Problem 1:  THE SYSTEM YOU ARE TASKED WITH BUILDING A SUSTEM TO CHECK WHETHER A PERSON IS ELIGIBLE TO VOTE. THE SYSTEM FOLLOWS THESE RULES:
1.. A PERSON MUST BE AT LEAST 18 YEARS OLD TO VOTE.
2.. IF THE PERSON IS A CITIZENS, THEY ARE ELIGIBLE TO VOTE
3.. IF THE PERSON IS NOT A CITIZEN BUT HAS PASSED citizenship test they are eligible to vote
4.. if the person is under 18 they cannot vote?


answer:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    
    <script>
        let age = parseInt(prompt("Enter your age:"))
        
        if(age>=18 ){
            let citizen = confirm("Are you a citizen?")
        let passedCitizenTest = confirm("Have you passed citizen test?")
            document.write("You are eligible to vote")
            
            if(age>=18 && !citizen && passedCitizenTest){
                document.write("You are eligible to vote")
            }
            
        }else{
            document.write("You are not eligible to vote")
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>


